---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Method • Historical Translation Project™">
  <Header />
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <div class="kicker">Method</div>
      <h1 class="mt-3 h-serif text-4xl sm:text-5xl">How we translate history into modern, targeted support</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-ink-900/70 leading-relaxed text-lg">
        Our formulations bridge historically proven approaches with modern-day data and studies to create targeted support supplements—
        designed for physician-directed use and compliant structure/function positioning.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card p-8">
        <div class="kicker">Step 1</div>
        <div class="mt-2 h-serif text-2xl">Text-first extraction</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/70 leading-relaxed">
          We start with primary sources—classical physicians, materia medica, and preventive frameworks—then translate recurring themes:
          digestion first, vitality distribution, resilience of terrain, and disciplined daily routines.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-8">
        <div class="kicker">Step 2</div>
        <div class="mt-2 h-serif text-2xl">Evidence signals</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/70 leading-relaxed">
          We map historical observations to modern physiology (not disease claims): motility, endothelial function, antioxidant response,
          immune modulation, and urinary comfort—supported with published reviews and mechanistic literature.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-8">
        <div class="kicker">Step 3</div>
        <div class="mt-2 h-serif text-2xl">Non-overlap design</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/70 leading-relaxed">
          Core formulas are built to avoid unnecessary duplication and contraindication risk. Add-ons are only curated when they add
          a distinct, complementary layer—while minimizing pill burden.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="card p-8">
        <div class="kicker">Step 4</div>
        <div class="mt-2 h-serif text-2xl">Physician-ready dossiers</div>
        <p class="mt-3 text-ink-900/70 leading-relaxed">
          Each program is documented with ingredient rationale, historical lineage, safety notes, and a publication list—so clinicians can
          evaluate fit within a patient’s broader plan of care.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
